    "Thus, given a directed (1)",
    "and weighted graph G with N nodes partitioned into C communities, the modularity can be defined as:",
    "Although several approaches could be used to partition the network, in this work we use the Louvain method (Blondel et al. 2008).",
    "Average clustering coefficient: The average clustering coefficient of a directed and weighted graph measures the degree to which nodes in the graph tend to cluster together, considering the weights of the edges.",
